rComments: Well put together, interesting and relevant lectures. As a professor, Chambers is understanding and caring. Can be a tough marker though- you gotta work for an A. Attendance is mandatory. You will likely not pass if you rely solely on readings. Gives practice questions before exams and assignments. Also no textbook! 10/10 would recommend.

One of my absolute favourite courses I've ever taken. The lectures were very interesting -- and VERY mandatory. The exams are very specific so you HAVE to go to class. If you go to every class the course is very easy.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures ', 'Graded by few things', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: One of my favourite professors so far! Great at relating course content to ongoing issues and his own life experience! 10/10 will be watching for his courses in the future
A really nice and interesting professor and lectures. Be ready to write ALOT during lectures.

The prof hosted no lectures and only used slide shows with no words on them just audio attached files which were not at all informative. Secondly, the guideline for the final exam was unclear and there was a lack of feedback given for previous assignments. The TA's for this class also marked on a bias curve and marks were deducted with no reasoning

Prof Chambers was incredible. Incredibly organized and presented info very enthusiastically. Definitely recommend getting him if you can. He cares about what he is teaching and inspires you to care too.

Does not negotiate grades, extremely hard marker, and would not recommend taking him. If possible take any other class than him, especially now that it is all virtual it makes his teaching style a lot more difficult.
Online due to COVID. Classes were very organized and interesting. His lectures are very clear and concise. He posted possibilities for exam questions beforehand. A fantastic prof. Highly recommend.

The prof himself is fine, but his TA is unreasonable and the grading criteria often conflicted with instructions. Unfortunately, this class was mandatory, or else I would have dropped it. Avoid it if you can.

Professor Chambers did a good job accommodating to the new way of learning. He always answered emails quickly and in good detail. I think if you just listen to the lectures it's an easy A- or A but the readings are the extra info that helps you get an A+. The content was generally interesting and I think this is a good elective to take and its easy
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I really enjoyed Chambers course. Was asynchronous because of covid and he used audio-embedded ppt slides instead. The material was really interesting! Easily accessible by email any time throughout the semester. We were graded by 4 articles summaries (he gives an example of an A+ quality one), 1 midterm and final. Would recommend!

Great prof and would absolutely recommend to anyone and everyone. Always available to answer my emails within a couple of hours and all classes were asynchronous so you can go at your own pace. 4 Article Summaries, a midterm (covers first part of term) and a final (covers second part of term ). One of the best electives out there and super fun!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Prof. Chambers really shows that he cares about his students. If you do the lectures and take notes, the class is an easy A. When you complete these assignments, he is not a tough grader but the grade you get is the grade you deserve
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: He's great!! All of the information is given through the lectures and you really do not need to do any of the required readings at all. He gives all of the exam questions in advance at the beginning of the semester and some of them will be on the exam. Show up and pass. He really cares about all of his students and gives a great amount of feedback

Professor Chambers is great. His class was hands-down the best I've taken in the COVID-era. It's very interesting to analyze pop culture from a political/social/economic standpoint, and Chambers does a terrific job of making these connections without soapboxing or going into tangents like other profs. CMN 2180 with Chambers is worth every minute.

I think he did a good job adjusting to having everything online and he posted lectures ahead of time. They were clear, concise, and mostly were very similar to the readings. The readings are very helpful in getting you an A+ in the class. I don't think this class is very modern though and talks about some older things but overall I would recommend

rComments: Prof Chambers is one of the best profs Ive had this first year. I send him quite a lot of questions and he always replies with clarification! He definitely cares about his students success. I wish I had him in person because I would love to get to know him! Im taking another one of his classes next sem because of how great he is :)

He is extremely clear about what he wants from you in examinations (even provides checklists). His textbook was cheap and you will use every sentence in it. He doesn't provide class notes so attendance is mandatory! Don't be shy to stay after class to chat with him, he is really nice and interesting. A real gem!

Overall, he's a great prof and knows what he's teaching. But there is a lot of discrepancy between him and the TA. The essay was worth 40% of our marks and the majority of the class did terrible on it. There was no rubric for it either. There's also no power points so all notes were taken during class. This is NOT an easy A class. Do not take it!!!

His class was a blast and super easy. Midterm and exam are 53 MCQ (not cumulative), 50% questions come from the lecture and 50% from the textbook. Reading the textbook is a must! He also requires 4, 1-page article summaries, with a super-easy marking scheme. I would definitely recommend!

Professor Chambers was an amazing professor - he is engaging, loves talking to his students, and is always available to discuss any questions. The format was midterm, 2 article analysis, and a final. As long as you attend class, he gives SEVERAL hints and teaches everything super clearly
WORST CLASS EVER. I am a straight A student and this class was just beyond disappointing. Content was so easy, but the professor is atrocious.

He gave us an exact layout of the essay he wanted, even the references and paragraph outline... pretty intense with no room for error or interpretation. Doesn't have much structure in his lectures and goes off on tangents, but very captivating and interesting to listen to.

I am in my fourth year, and this prof. is THE BEST prof i have had. He is clear about is criteria and EXTREMELY helpful for those who genuinely want to do well in the class. The class is an easy GPA booster if you are willing to put in the work, make sure to take good notes in class to help you fill out your study guide. Wish he taught more classes

The most straight forward class I've ever taken in my life. Just show up and do the readings. He summarizes everything in class and does not put anything on the exam that we haven't talked about. Midterm and final are MCQ worth 40% each. Written assignment is worth 20%. You choose two readings from the course pack and summarize each one in one page

His exams are almost all based on what's discussed in class, so as long as you do the readings in the syllabus and go to the lectures, you'll do well. Professor Chambers genuinely cares about his students and is an overall great prof.

Chambers' made lectures interesting but is very stubborn. The essay given was given with how he expected the layout and already what references to use but has high expectations and is a harsh grader on the essay. The exams are super hard multiple choice that some questions do not match his material. DO NOT RECOMMEND!

Professor Chambers is awesome! He genuinely cares about his students and if you put in the hard work and effort then IT WILL pay off. For this class we only had to do a midterm, essay, and a final. The essay was worth around 40% but, he holds office hours so you can go and see him for advice and corrections. Put in effort and you will succeed!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Chambers was great! However, the marking scheme was unclear for the paper we had to write for the class. There was a lot of discrepancy between the marking of him and his TA. Loved this prof! I'm not in communications but thoroughly enjoyed this class. I find Chambers conveyed the material really well and kept all the lectures interesting with enthusiasm. He is very fair. The mark you get, it's the mark you deserve. It prepares you for your futur essay. If you know the subject, you can EASILY answer all the questions on the exam. They are not tricky. Best prof I've ever had. We have a lot of readings, but they are really good! I learned a lot in his class. He's inspirational. I would recommend it! His lectures are amazing. When you understand the lectures, the exams are really easy. When you know it, you can clearly see that there is only one answer that is good (multiple choice). AMAZING PROF
Best teacher I've ever had. He's inspiring. I learned so much in SCS 1150. There is a lot of readings, but they are really good and on the subject. I would recommend it!!

An amazing professor. Make sure you do the readings and go to class, but he inspired me to minor in international development. As long as you take thorough notes and go to class, youre golden. Really looking forward to having him next semester, hes a great prof and a very caring and compassionate man.

Death and dying is hands down the best HSS course I've taken in my four years of undergrad, and prof chambers played a huge role in making this class enjoyable. Lectures are really interesting but you have to take notes, each lecture also has corresponding readings. Take this course.
I really liked professor Chambers, his class was very interesting and gave me a new perspective on many social sciences issues.

Incredible prof with inspirational guest speakers. The course really makes you reflect on social issues. To get a good grade all you need to do is go to class, take notes and do all of the readings. BTW class discussions are amazing.

Great Professor! Would highly recommend taking a class with him. He genuinely cares about his students learning and makes sure they have the required knowledge if they put the effort in. Don't hesitate to visit his office hours as they are extremely helpful and he makes his expectations 100% clear.

rComments: I would HIGHLY recommend Professor Chambers. He was funny, exciting and charismatic. He obviously loves teaching and he made the class extremely interesting. I had many interesting conversations outside of class with him as well. He's really amazing!
Super fun lectures. Really engaging.

Professor Chambers is an extremely helpful and passionate professor! He provides a lot of guidance with class material and is super friendly. During class says his quizzes and exams are easy and when he gives samples questions they are but during the actual exam he tricks you! He posts his own material he wrote online so you can read it but he goes through it in class. Overall I would change my program before taking him ever again

I had Chambers for two courses this semester and he is amazing. Tests can be tricky you have to really know your stuff as he makes the options a-e, BUT he avoids "all the above" "a & c" type of answers. Pop culture was so interesting I wish I could take it again!

i don't think he is the best prof. in uottawa. Was an extremely boring class!  if you are able to spend hours every night reading useless amounts of pages and studying your hardest for this specific course the n go ahead.

A godsend. Clear, interesting, and very expressive in class. Willing to help if you just ask in his office hours! Exams were a little tricky (MC A-E) but he provides lots of guidance with regards to their contents, and has bonus questions. Very good at stimulating discussion!

rComments: Loves showing YouTube clips in class to help solidify points, but not the most technologically savvy. Loves talking about music in the 1970s. Amazing prof, lectures are always enthusiastic! does not lecture with power point he lectures off a sheet and uploads the same sheet onto blackboard bolded with important terms. essay was difficult but he will sit one on one with you during office hours and help you! he's a great professor and he enjoys what he is doing i strongly recommend him!
Super opinionated and ridiculously specific on his essay. Questions in class, if you dared, were pretty much deflected and replaced with more opinionated statements. Would not recommend.

Amazing prof. My favorite professor so far in university. He is so helpful on essays if you go talk to him! And the readings are a lot, but they are interesting!

THE MOST AMAZING PROFESSOR IN THE WHOLE DEPARTMENT OF COMMUNICATIONS!! Media Ethics was the best class I have taken in all my three years!! Interesting lectures and all the notes are online (essay style), the content was really interesting and I learned a lot. Can truly say in my last year of university that he is one of the best. He is very engaging, lectures are actually interesting, and he wants students to get something out of the class. If you have the chance to take a course with Professor Chambers, do it. I will always remember him.

This professor changed my academic outlook and showed the real value of having a professor who truly cared about the content they were teaching and the matter in which they were teaching it. best course I took in university and that was because of having him as the teacher.

So much respect for this professor. Does not use a TA, but meticulously marks all exams and papers himself, giving abundant amounts of feedback and constructive criticism. Very knowledgeable on what he teaches and provides detailed notes of his lectures. Highly recommend!

This is by far the best professor I have ever had. Never seen someone so willing to help his students, such a nice change! Take advantage of his office hours, you can learn so much just by going to speak with him! Ottawa U needs more profs like him, take his class if you get the opportunity:)!!

This man is BRILLIANT and an absolutely AMAZING prof. He's impartial to all opinions. We discussed the broadest range of topics. Reading is heavy, however, every piece is intriguing. AMAZING prof! The best class yet! And the readings are really interesting not boring like the other typical class text book. His exams are easy if you read the readings and go to class. I recommend him time and time again as he realizes that students are humans and need help sometimes.

Professor Chambers is one of the best professors I've had in my four years of university. His style basically gives everybody an A+, but you HAVE to do the work. Very inspirational, passionate about his work. But exams are very hard, with most of the questions not focusing on main theories or topics discussed in class. Have to really focus on the readings because the smallest elements are usually what you get tested on.
Nice prof. Just do the readings and you will pass his class
He is COOL! A great guy! Enthusiastic about the lectures and readings.  He is funny, and his lectures are pretty interesting.  His multiple choice tests are pretty hard.

Phenomenal lectures. Pleasure to listen to. Essay has very strict guidelines - almost as if it is not my own.  Brought it great Guest Speakers, got me more interested in subject. Class is very interesting because of professor, but seems very difficult to get a good grade in.

First class is intimidating and seems like lots of work, but it is SO easy to achieve a good grade! Prof provides all questions before exams, and answers are easy to find in textbook/class notes. 2 exams and one essay for this class. Tries to scare everyone on the first day but so glad I stayed in the class. He posted notes online, he told us all the questions that could possibly be on the exam...as long as you want an A you can get one! Essay is the toughest part.

Chambers is a very intellectual; fortunately, he is also humble and completely reasonable in expectations. The essay does not leave students with a lot of latitude, you must follow his guidelines by the letter, and the TA is very harsh.
